The manual safety cannot be moved and the trigger cannot be pulled. To disengage: simply rotate the key one-quarter turn back. 989,http://www.armslist.com/posts/2524989,For Sale:  VZ 24 1938 Marked 8 mm Czechoslovakian Mauser,"West Winston-Salem, Lewisville Clemmons area, Winston Salem, North Carolina",$ 350,"Listed On: Friday, April 4, 2014",Rifles,Mauser                                                                                ,8mm Mauser                                                                                ,Bolt Action                                                                                ,Rifle,"I picked this rifle up in a collection, and since I already have 2 VZ 24s, my wife says I don't need another.  The rifle is the highly acclaimed Czech version of the large ring 98 Mauser.  1938 date is stamped on the receiver crest which is not ground like many on this model.  The serial number is: E10129. The number on the bolt does not match the rifle, which is typical for the VZ 24.  The stock appears to have been refinished very nicely, there are very few dings and minor scratches in the finish, but no cracks and the wood has a very nice pattern with what appears to be an original type of oil finish.

The rifle has both of the trigger guard capture screws, and there are no obvious missing screws or parts that I can see other than the cleaning rod.  The rifle includes a front sight hood, although it is not shown in the photos.  There no sling or bayonet included in this sale.

I have not shot this rifle, but the other 2 I have are great shooters, and neither has a bore this nice.  The bore is in very good shape, shiny with minimal pitting and well defined grooves, which is unusual for VZ 24s. The muzzle crown looks good and the rifle easily passes the ""bullet"" test with about 5 mm of bullet showing.
The rifle is import marked on the right side of the front of the barrel in small letters.  No markings are peened.  The bluing is about 80% by my estimate.
I've tried to describe the rifle to the best of my ability, but if you have questions or need to see more photos I can email them.  Armslist limits me to posting 3 photos.
Please contact me via email if you are interested.  I'm looking to do a FTF sale around the Winston-Salem area.  I can travel some if necessary to meet you."
